\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. C. salonitana} Vis., {\i Flora} ({\i Regensb.}) {\b 12} (Ergänz. 1): 23 (1829) ({\i C. collina} sensu Sibth. & Sm., non L.). Stems up to 100 cm, sparingly branched. Lower leaves 1- to 2-pinnatisect; middle cauline pinnatifid, with obovate to lanceolate, mucronulate segments; rhachis winged. Involucral bracts broadly ovate; appendages pale yellow, with an apical spine c. 3 mm (up to 40 mm in var.{\i  macracantha} DC.). Florets bright yellow, rarely purple, the outer slightly longer than the inner. Achenes c. 5 mm, pubescent; pappus 7-9 mm, reddish. 2n = 20, 40. {\i Stony places and grassland. S.E. & E.C. Europe.} Al Bu ?Cr Gr Hu Ju Rm Rs (K).
