\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13. C. centauroides} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 918 (1753). Stems up to 100 cm, sparingly branched above. Leaves white-tomentose, glabrescent, lyrate; lateral segments at least 3 mm wide, ovate-oblong, the terminal up to 7 × 10 mm, broadly ovate. Involucre up to 25 mm in diameter, globose; bracts broadly ovate; appendages broadly decurrent, with margin c. 0·5 mm wide, with an apical spine up to 20 mm; fimbriae c. 2 mm. Florets yellow with black veins. Achenes 4 mm; pappus about as long as achene.{\i  Mountain woods. S. Italy.} It.
